text:
There was a short queue (a few person in line) on a Tuesday lunch time. Many food choices, but managed to only try the Dang Gui Roasted Duck rice this time.

Portion is big and price is reasonable at $4.30 but taste average. Rice is a bit lumpy and sticky kind which is not to my personal liking.

I ordered the ABC soup (no rice). Good value for money ($3:80). For a small bowl, there were 4 pieces of pork rib, several pieces of potatoes and carrots. Soup was very tasty but not salty. The pork rib was soft and tender. Great for a light lunch.

This roasted delights store has changed over the years. This one is quite good, the uncle says "Enjoy your meal" to all his customers. The food is 9/10, chicken WILL have bones but I ordered the 3 combo meat meal, honestly I find it eorth the money. Add egg if you're feeling extra hungry.

Meats are good
Noodle not good
